texts.tID: Always referring to himself in the 3rd person, Coach believes in shouting first and asking questions later – said Coach.\n\nABILITY: Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed.
texts.eN: Always referring to himself in the 3rd person, Coach believes in shouting first and asking questions later – said Coach.\n\nABILITY: Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed.

texts.tID: Straight outta Centre Court, Lady Grenade's preferred greeting is a savage chest bump she likes to call the Grand Slam.\n\nABILITY: Serves up a volley of grenades.
texts.eN: Straight outta Centre Court, Lady Grenade's preferred greeting is a savage chest bump she likes to call the Grand Slam.\n\nABILITY: Serves up a volley of grenades.

texts.tID: Notorious for a' firin' his laser, B.I.G. also loves to read archaeology novels while imprisoned inside the robot dinosaur.\n\nABILITY: Jumps forward and lands with a S.T.O.M.P.
texts.eN: Notorious for a' firin' his laser, B.I.G. also loves to read archaeology novels while imprisoned inside the robot dinosaur.\n\nABILITY: Jumps forward and lands with a S.T.O.M.P.

texts.tID: Being raised by bears gave Bearman a unique perspective on life, but he never learned to talk so no one knows what it is.\n\nABILITY: Charges forward, smashing through and into things.
texts.eN: Being raised by bears gave Bearman a unique perspective on life, but he never learned to talk so no one knows what it is.\n\nABILITY: Charges forward, smashing through and into things.

texts.tID: From the safety of her weird egg tank, Mother runs her tech startup. It takes a bold CEO to add a cannon to their office.\n\nABILITY: Hires a couple of loyal Henchmen.
texts.eN: From the safety of her weird egg tank, Mother runs her tech startup. It takes a bold CEO to add a cannon to their office.\n\nABILITY: Hires a couple of loyal Henchmen.

texts.tID: Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed with words of encouragement, delivered in an uplifting tone.
texts.eN: Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed with words of encouragement, delivered in an uplifting tone.

texts.tID: Heals your units with some sort of green energy... and a 5-step healing program! Expect more emotionally stable troops after use.
texts.eN: Heals your units with some sort of green energy... and a 5-step healing program! Expect more emotionally stable troops after use.

texts.tID: Show that you mean business by pulling an object out of orbit and landing it on the enemy! Deals HUGE damage in a large area.
texts.eN: Show that you mean business by pulling an object out of orbit and landing it on the enemy! Deals HUGE damage in a large area.

texts.tID: Makes your units invisible for a few seconds, even while attacking. Everyone's a ninja!
texts.eN: Makes your units invisible for a few seconds, even while attacking. Everyone's a ninja!

texts.tID: Drop an arcade machine on them like a total rockstar. Damages enemy units in a small area and destroys obstacles.
texts.eN: Drop an arcade machine on them like a total rockstar. Damages enemy units in a small area and destroys obstacles.

texts.tID: Drops two Troopers on the enemy. Hawaiian shirts and hairy legs falling from the sky – geronimo!
texts.eN: Drops two Troopers on the enemy. Hawaiian shirts and hairy legs falling from the sky – geronimo!

texts.tID: Freezes enemy units and sends a chilling message: someone left the fridge door open overnight and the yogurt has gone bad...
texts.eN: Freezes enemy units and sends a chilling message: someone left the fridge door open overnight and the yogurt has gone bad...

texts.tID: Bread and butter of warfare! Attacks air and ground at short range. Cool under pressure, but watch out for grenades!
texts.eN: Bread and butter of warfare! Attacks air and ground at short range. Cool under pressure, but watch out for grenades!

texts.tID: Put them at the front to soak up damage with their riot shields – but really it's their healthy skepticism that keeps them safe.
texts.eN: Put them at the front to soak up damage with their riot shields – but really it's their healthy skepticism that keeps them safe.

texts.tID: Ex-baseball pitcher putting those throwing skills to good use! Medium range and best against groups of enemies.
texts.eN: Ex-baseball pitcher putting those throwing skills to good use! Medium range and best against groups of enemies.

texts.tID: This absolute unit crushes obstacles in its path and deals area damage at medium range. Also works part-time for a rideshare company.
texts.eN: This absolute unit crushes obstacles in its path and deals area damage at medium range. Also works part-time for a rideshare company.

texts.tID: Long range, area damage to both air and ground units, plus extra damage to Tanks and buildings! Previously a world champion arm wrestler.
texts.eN: Long range, area damage to both air and ground units, plus extra damage to Tanks and buildings! Previously a world champion arm wrestler.

texts.tID: It's a building-targeting Gorilla with a GIANT wrench! Why did they make a wrench this big? What does he do with it? So many questions...
texts.eN: It's a building-targeting Gorilla with a GIANT wrench! Why did they make a wrench this big? What does he do with it? So many questions...

texts.tID: Fast moving, medium ranged and can fly over obstacles. Can't be targeted by certain troops or defenses. Blue hair is the new pink!
texts.eN: Fast moving, medium ranged and can fly over obstacles. Can't be targeted by certain troops or defenses. Blue hair is the new pink!

texts.tID: Eyebrow model by day, Hotshot by night. He moves fast and blasts anything in front of him. His shotgun doubles as a selfie stick.
texts.eN: Eyebrow model by day, Hotshot by night. He moves fast and blasts anything in front of him. His shotgun doubles as a selfie stick.

texts.tID: His attack passes through and damages all enemies in its path! This makes him terrifying beyond the capacity for rational thought.
texts.eN: His attack passes through and damages all enemies in its path! This makes him terrifying beyond the capacity for rational thought.

texts.tID: The van parks up, then the Plumbers pile out – like an army of handyman ants who won't fix your pipes.
texts.eN: The van parks up, then the Plumbers pile out – like an army of handyman ants who won't fix your pipes.

texts.tID: Deals long range, area damage to ground units. Side hustles as a grilled cheese sandwich food truck on weekends.
texts.eN: Deals long range, area damage to ground units. Side hustles as a grilled cheese sandwich food truck on weekends.

texts.tID: Invisible until he attacks! Moves very fast and carries a box of crickets to mask his footsteps. So sneaky.
texts.eN: Invisible until he attacks! Moves very fast and carries a box of crickets to mask his footsteps. So sneaky.

texts.tID: Briefly stuns enemies with each punch. Enjoys a good brawl almost as much as a soft bamboo tank top.
texts.eN: Briefly stuns enemies with each punch. Enjoys a good brawl almost as much as a soft bamboo tank top.

texts.tID: Shoots a jet of flame at short range, effective against groups of enemies. Always looking for a new audience to roast with his stand-up routine.
texts.eN: Shoots a jet of flame at short range, effective against groups of enemies. Always looking for a new audience to roast with his stand-up routine.

texts.tID: Deals area damage up close with his nunchucks, which double as drumsticks when playing for his smooth jazz band Hot Potato.
texts.eN: Deals area damage up close with his nunchucks, which double as drumsticks when playing for his smooth jazz band Hot Potato.

texts.tID: Deals area damage at very long range. Fun.
texts.eN: Deals area damage at very long range. Fun.

texts.tID: They come in pairs, like socks, but are less friendly to your feet. Deals area damage to nearby ground units.
texts.eN: They come in pairs, like socks, but are less friendly to your feet. Deals area damage to nearby ground units.

texts.tID: Deals more area damage than a Mine, but in a smaller radius. It's da bomb!
texts.eN: Deals more area damage than a Mine, but in a smaller radius. It's da bomb!

texts.tID: Block pathways and guide enemy ground troops... TO THEIR DOOM! Ahahaha!
texts.eN: Block pathways and guide enemy ground troops... TO THEIR DOOM! Ahahaha!

texts.tID: Targets air and ground at long range with lethal efficiency. Another Henchman making Mother proud.
texts.eN: Targets air and ground at long range with lethal efficiency. Another Henchman making Mother proud.

texts.tID: Its barrels spin fast, then faster, then fastest! Perfect for taking down big targets. Meanwhile, the Henchman says “Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaah!”
texts.eN: Its barrels spin fast, then faster, then fastest! Perfect for taking down big targets. Meanwhile, the Henchman says “Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaah!”

texts.tID: Caution! Plumbers at work. Approach at your own risk.
texts.eN: Caution! Plumbers at work. Approach at your own risk.

texts.tID: Freezes air and ground units... and gravity apparently!? Cool, huh?
texts.eN: Freezes air and ground units... and gravity apparently!? Cool, huh?

texts.tID: Shoots a human-size ball of plasma that passes through and damages all enemies in its path! Range is from long to very very very long.
texts.eN: Shoots a human-size ball of plasma that passes through and damages all enemies in its path! Range is from long to very very very long.

texts.tID: Pops up, zaps multiple targets at once, then slinks away. Dreams of becoming a disco ball one day.
texts.eN: Pops up, zaps multiple targets at once, then slinks away. Dreams of becoming a disco ball one day.

texts.tID: Launches homing rockets from a questionably small silo in the ground. Effective against a trio of units.
texts.eN: Launches homing rockets from a questionably small silo in the ground. Effective against a trio of units.

texts.tID: Armed with tasers that slow and a strong desire to please Mother, they won't stop until you're toast. Burnt toast.
texts.eN: Armed with tasers that slow and a strong desire to please Mother, they won't stop until you're toast. Burnt toast.

texts.tID: Flies over obstacles and drops bombs from its steel jaws – look out below! Piloted by a 7-foot Henchman who didn't make the basketball team.
texts.eN: Flies over obstacles and drops bombs from its steel jaws – look out below! Piloted by a 7-foot Henchman who didn't make the basketball team.

texts.eN: It's a ninja in a box, but if you get close... it becomes a ninja out of a box!

texts.tID: So what did he tell you about us...? And can you really trust a dude in a dinosaur costume? We've seen him eat PB&J sandwiches in there.
texts.eN: So what did he tell you about us...? And can you really trust a dude in a dinosaur costume? We've seen him eat PB&J sandwiches in there.

texts.tID: Hello again. You wanna get mega rich, huh? We can help. Just sign here.. We'll take your silence as a non-verbal agreement.
texts.eN: Hello again. You wanna get mega rich, huh? We can help. Just sign here.. We'll take your silence as a non-verbal agreement.

texts.tID: What's more valuable than gold? LOTS of gold. There's a global gold rush happening and you do not want to miss out.
texts.eN: What's more valuable than gold? LOTS of gold. There's a global gold rush happening and you do not want to miss out.

texts.tID: Getting mega rich ain't easy, but we've got a few tricks to share. Start by joining an active Team, OK?
texts.eN: Getting mega rich ain't easy, but we've got a few tricks to share. Start by joining an active Team, OK?

texts.tID: Firstly, be a good Teammate. Chatty, friendly, etc. Earn their trust, ya know?
texts.eN: Firstly, be a good Teammate. Chatty, friendly, etc. Earn their trust, ya know?

texts.tID: Secondly, donate to their bonus defense research. You gotta spend gold to make gold.
texts.eN: Secondly, donate to their bonus defense research. You gotta spend gold to make gold.

texts.tID: Thirdly, join your Team's Daily Domination. This is where you can scoop up a lot more gold, and fame.
texts.eN: Thirdly, join your Team's Daily Domination. This is where you can scoop up a lot more gold, and fame.

texts.tID: Now that we've helped you, you will help us. Just like it says in our agreement. We'll be in touch.
texts.eN: Now that we've helped you, you will help us. Just like it says in our agreement. We'll be in touch.

texts.tID: Someone has stolen the manuscript for our next archaeology novel. It's called Dig Lemon Boat Ages. We need it back.
texts.eN: Someone has stolen the manuscript for our next archaeology novel. It's called Dig Lemon Boat Ages. We need it back.

texts.tID: Just a peanut and some floss? …
texts.eN: We've found the manuscript. There's jam on it. Probably Bearman. Find out what else he took. Check his pockets.

ability_cards.name: Rage
ability_cards.infoTID: Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed with words of encouragement, delivered in an uplifting tone.

ability_cards.name: Heal
ability_cards.infoTID: Heals your units with some sort of green energy... and a 5-step healing program! Expect more emotionally stable troops after use.

ability_cards.name: ArcadeDrop
ability_cards.infoTID: Drop an arcade machine on them like a total rockstar. Damages enemy units in a small area and destroys obstacles.

ability_cards.name: Invisibility
ability_cards.infoTID: Makes your units invisible for a few seconds, even while attacking. Everyone's a ninja!

ability_cards.name: Paratrooper
ability_cards.infoTID: Drops two Troopers on the enemy. Hawaiian shirts and hairy legs falling from the sky – geronimo!

ability_cards.name: Bombard
ability_cards.infoTID: Show that you mean business by pulling an object out of orbit and landing it on the enemy! Deals HUGE damage in a large area.

ability_cards.name: Fridge
ability_cards.infoTID: Freezes enemy units and sends a chilling message: someone left the fridge door open overnight and the yogurt has gone bad...

commander_cards.name: SoldierCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: Always referring to himself in the 3rd person, Coach believes in shouting first and asking questions later – said Coach.\n\nABILITY: Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed.

commander_cards.name: GrenadeCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: Straight outta Centre Court, Lady Grenade's preferred greeting is a savage chest bump she likes to call the Grand Slam.\n\nABILITY: Serves up a volley of grenades.

commander_cards.name: DinoCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: Notorious for a' firin' his laser, B.I.G. also loves to read archaeology novels while imprisoned inside the robot dinosaur.\n\nABILITY: Jumps forward and lands with a S.T.O.M.P.

commander_cards.name: BearCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: Being raised by bears gave Bearman a unique perspective on life, but he never learned to talk so no one knows what it is.\n\nABILITY: Charges forward, smashing through and into things.

commander_cards.name: EggCommander
commander_cards.infoTID: From the safety of her weird egg tank, Mother runs her tech startup. It takes a bold CEO to add a cannon to their office.\n\nABILITY: Hires a couple of loyal Henchmen.

defence_cards.name: Mortar
defence_cards.infoTID: Deals area damage at very long range. Fun.

defence_cards.name: Mine
defence_cards.infoTID: They come in pairs, like socks, but are less friendly to your feet. Deals area damage to nearby ground units.

defence_cards.name: Wall
defence_cards.infoTID: Block pathways and guide enemy ground troops... TO THEIR DOOM! Ahahaha!

defence_cards.name: Wall_H
defence_cards.infoTID: Block pathways and guide enemy ground troops... TO THEIR DOOM! Ahahaha!

defence_cards.name: Cannon
defence_cards.infoTID: Targets air and ground at long range with lethal efficiency. Another Henchman making Mother proud.

defence_cards.name: PlumberHut
defence_cards.infoTID: Caution! Plumbers at work. Approach at your own risk.

defence_cards.name: Cake
defence_cards.infoTID: Surprise! It's your birthday. Your final birthday.

defence_cards.name: Gatling
defence_cards.infoTID: Its barrels spin fast, then faster, then fastest! Perfect for taking down big targets. Meanwhile, the Henchman says “Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaah!”

defence_cards.name: Bomb
defence_cards.infoTID: Deals more area damage than a Mine, but in a smaller radius. It's da bomb!

defence_cards.name: FreezeTrap
defence_cards.infoTID: Freezes air and ground units... and gravity apparently!? Cool, huh?

defence_cards.name: Plasmagun
defence_cards.infoTID: Shoots a human-size ball of plasma that passes through and damages all enemies in its path! Range is from long to very very very long.

defence_cards.name: BlackNinja
defence_cards.infoTID: It's a ninja in a box, but if you get close... it becomes a ninja out of a box!

defence_cards.name: Tesla
defence_cards.infoTID: Pops up, zaps multiple targets at once, then slinks away. Dreams of becoming a disco ball one day.

defence_cards.name: RocketPlatform
defence_cards.infoTID: Launches homing rockets from a questionably small silo in the ground. Effective against a trio of units.

resources.name: Gems
resources.popOverTID: Gems are the most valuable resource in the game!

resources.name: Key
resources.popOverTID:
Keys are required to receive box from battle!

Next Key:
<time>

troop_cards.name: Soldier
troop_cards.infoTID: Bread and butter of warfare! Attacks air and ground at short range. Cool under pressure, but watch out for grenades!

troop_cards.name: Grenade
troop_cards.infoTID: Ex-baseball pitcher putting those throwing skills to good use! Medium range and best against groups of enemies.

troop_cards.name: Shield
troop_cards.infoTID: Put them at the front to soak up damage with their riot shields – but really it's their healthy skepticism that keeps them safe.

troop_cards.name: Tank
troop_cards.infoTID: This absolute unit crushes obstacles in its path and deals area damage at medium range. Also works part-time for a rideshare company.

troop_cards.name: Bazooka
troop_cards.infoTID: Long range, area damage to both air and ground units, plus extra damage to Tanks and buildings! Previously a world champion arm wrestler.

troop_cards.name: PlumberVan
troop_cards.infoTID: The van parks up, then the Plumbers pile out – like an army of handyman ants who won't fix your pipes.

troop_cards.name: Jetpack
troop_cards.infoTID: Fast moving, medium ranged and can fly over obstacles. Can't be targeted by certain troops or defenses. Blue hair is the new pink!

troop_cards.name: Gorilla
troop_cards.infoTID: It's a building-targeting Gorilla with a GIANT wrench! Why did they make a wrench this big? What does he do with it? So many questions...

troop_cards.name: Shotgun
troop_cards.infoTID: Eyebrow model by day, Hotshot by night. He moves fast and blasts anything in front of him. His shotgun doubles as a selfie stick.

troop_cards.name: Laser
troop_cards.infoTID: His attack passes through and damages all enemies in its path! This makes him terrifying beyond the capacity for rational thought.

troop_cards.name: Boxer
troop_cards.infoTID: Briefly stuns enemies with each punch. Enjoys a good brawl almost as much as a soft bamboo tank top.

troop_cards.name: Tazer
troop_cards.infoTID: Armed with tasers that slow and a strong desire to please Mother, they won't stop until you're toast. Burnt toast.

troop_cards.name: Helipod
troop_cards.infoTID: Flies over obstacles and drops bombs from its steel jaws – look out below! Piloted by a 7-foot Henchman who didn't make the basketball team.

troop_cards.name: Flamethrower
troop_cards.infoTID: Shoots a jet of flame at short range, effective against groups of enemies. Always looking for a new audience to roast with his stand-up routine.

troop_cards.name: BombardTank
troop_cards.infoTID: Deals long range, area damage to ground units. Side hustles as a grilled cheese sandwich food truck on weekends.

troop_cards.name: KungFu
troop_cards.infoTID: Deals area damage up close with his nunchucks, which double as drumsticks when playing for his smooth jazz band Hot Potato.

troop_cards.name: WhiteNinja
troop_cards.infoTID: Invisible until he attacks! Moves very fast and carries a box of crickets to mask his footsteps. So sneaky.

tutorials_home.name: Welcome
tutorials_home.commanderText: This is your camp! Here, you can chill out and prepare for your next battle.

tutorials_home.name: Welcome2
tutorials_home.commanderText: Hit the ATTACK button when you're thirsty for more gold!

tutorials_home.name: UnlockAirdrop
tutorials_home.commanderText: First AIRDROP found. Neat!\nLet's ATTACK again and try it out.

tutorials_home.name: UpgradeHQ_Dude
tutorials_home.commanderText: Now you can upgrade your HQ to find new TROOPS, and make it look cooler!

tutorials_home.name: UpgradeHelicopter_Dude
tutorials_home.commanderText: You've got a CHOPPER! Rad. Upgrade it to carry more TROOPS into battle.

tutorials_home.name: Defence_Dude
tutorials_home.commanderText: Gold – we need more gold! \n\nTo produce GOLD we need to find a GOLD MINE! Let's do it now!

tutorials_npc.name: NPC1_Intro
tutorials_npc.commanderText: Ready to kick butt and get mega rich?\nGood – attack this GOLD MINE!

tutorials_npc.name: NPC3_Intro
tutorials_npc.commanderText: AIRDROPS can be used to take out a group of enemies. Let 'em have it!

tutorials_npc.name: NPC4_Intro
tutorials_npc.commanderText: Last training base, then you're ready.\nWelcome to the RUSH WARS!

tutorials_npc.name: Commander_Info
tutorials_npc.commanderText: Your new COMMANDER is there on the battlefield!\n\nYou can move him around and activate his ability during the battle!

tid.TIP_STORY1: So what did he tell you about us...? And can you really trust a dude in a dinosaur costume? We've seen him eat PB&J sandwiches in there.
tid.TIP_STORY2: Hello again. You wanna get mega rich, huh? We can help. Just sign here.. We'll take your silence as a non-verbal agreement.
tid.TIP_STORY3: What's more valuable than gold? LOTS of gold. There's a global gold rush happening and you do not want to miss out.
tid.TIP_STORY4: Getting mega rich ain't easy, but we've got a few tricks to share. Start by joining an active Team, OK?
tid.TIP_STORY5: Firstly, be a good Teammate. Chatty, friendly, etc. Earn their trust, ya know?
tid.TIP_STORY6: Secondly, donate to their bonus defense research. You gotta spend gold to make gold.
tid.TIP_STORY7: Thirdly, join your Team's Daily Domination. This is where you can scoop up a lot more gold, and fame.
tid.TIP_STORY8: Now that we've helped you, you will help us. Just like it says in our agreement. We'll be in touch.
tid.TIP_STORY9: Someone has stolen the manuscript for our next archaeology novel. It's called Dig Lemon Boat Ages. We need it back.
tid.TIP_STORY10: Just a peanut and some floss? …
tid.TIP1: At the end of a battle, unused cards get turned into bonus gold!
tid.TIP2: Join a Team to face off against other Teams from around the globe in a Domination!
tid.TIP3: When you flee from a wolf, you run into a bear.
tid.TIP4: You can research a bonus defense if you're in a Team.
tid.TIP5: Exploding barrels don't damage your own troops. Phew!
tid.TIP6: Airdrops don't damage your own troops.
tid.TIP7: Storm Area 54, they can't stop all of us.
tid.TIP8: Free Boxes are delivered to your camp every few hours. Sweet!
tid.TIP9: You gain every Star you defend at your Gold Mine.
tid.TIP10: Commanders have special abilities that can be used multiple times during a battle.
tid.TIP11: Upgrading your Chopper allows it to travel farther and take your troops to new locations!
tid.TIP14: You can save troops and airdrops to deploy DURING a battle!
tid.TIP15: Have you noticed those suspicious looking hazmat dudes hanging around?
tid.TIP16: Coach's special ability boosts your units' attack speed and move speed.
tid.TIP17: Lady Grenade's special ability serves up a volley of grenades in front of her.
tid.TIP18: Bearman's special ability makes him charge forward, smashing through and into things.
tid.TIP19: Mother's special ability hires a couple of loyal Henchmen to do her bidding.
tid.TIP20: B.I.G.'s special ability allows him to jump forward and land with a S.T.O.M.P.
